itest
=====================

This is a small tools to test seco/v2x api bridge on the seco_libs layer

Supported Arch: x86_64, arm64

Supported OS: Linux

cmake_minimum_required 3.10

Setup
------------

To setup submodule run + `./b -s`

Build
------------

build for Host ()
+ ex: run `./b -H x86_64`

build for target using toolchain from env
+ ex: run `./b -H arm64`

build for target using a toolchain
+ ex: run `./b -T /opt/toolchains/gcc-linaro-7.5.0-2019.12-x86_64_aarch64-linux-gnu/bin/aarch64-linux-gnu -E /opt/toolchains/gcc-linaro-7.5.0-2019.12-x86_64_aarch64-linux-gnu/aarch64-linux-gnu`

Build script Help
+ run `./b -h`

build script:
+ -h: print this help
+ -H <ARCH>: build itest for host (arm64 or x86_64)
+ -S <path>: path to seco_libs
+ -T <path>: path to the toolchain cc  (ex:/opt/toolchains/gcc-linaro-7.5.0-2019.12-x86_64_aarch64-linux-gnu/bin/aarch64-linux-gnu)
+ -E <path>: path to the toolchain env (ex:/opt/toolchains/gcc-linaro-7.5.0-2019.12-x86_64_aarch64-linux-gnu/aarch64-linux-gnu)
+ -f: force rebuild static lib json-c
+ -s: init git submodule (lib json-c)

